It is palliative care, which is given when there is nothing else to do.
To make death more comfortable.
In Québec, there is a palliative care bed for 11,700 people.
It's very little when we know that we all end up dying one day.
Here, life continues in the best possible conditions, explains Dr. Christiane Martel, one of the doctors at the house.
Whether at the level of physical, emotional or spiritual comfort.
At the time of death, we will agree to provide oral care to brandy or Pepsi, depending on the request.
Diabetics will no longer be required to control their sugar levels.
Death is part of everyday life.
Last night, we served a beer to Mr. X, who died overnight.
