At Victor-Gadbois’ home, the days follow but do not resemble each other.
Alongside an old 93-year-old man who enjoys his last family gathering in the yard, well-knitted in his pillows while dripping in his honor, a young 36-year-old man tragically dies, surrounded by his parents, his wife and his two young children, after having tried everything for him.
