Four generations of small peas grown in orbit did not differ in any way from terrestrial varieties.
Then we put insects into orbit, small breeding drosophile flies.
In 1979, cauliflower eggs were sent into space to see how a heavier embryo developed.
We get a perfectly normal chick at the exit.
Then, the problems begin.
