The Imbongi choir repeats in Heidelberg, and the AIDS orphans in Swaziland are delighted to have come.
Here is the story of a link that goes far beyond a distance of 8,733 kilometers.
First, one taps the foot: cowboy boots, sneakers, boots for ladies and moccasins for men look for the rhythm by hitting the floor of the foot. Very quickly, they find it.
One, two, three, four.
