Hagman played Ewing as a corrupt and insatiable man with a charismatic smile: a dishonest entrepreneur and an unfaithful husband who was trying to intern his alcoholic wife Sue Ellen (Linda Gray).
“I know what it would take as an epitaph for J.R,” Hagman said in 1988.
We should write, "This is the honest citizen J.R. Ewing."
Here's the only part he's lost.
